Two women who were part of a group that repeatedly searched Mississippi 's capital city for black people to assault were sentenced Thursday to multiple years in the 2011 hate killing of 47-year-old James Craig Anderson .
U.S. District Judge Henry T. Wingate on Thursday sentenced Shelbie Brooke Richards , 21 to eight years in prison on one count each of conspiracy to commit a hate crime and concealing the crime by lying to police .
